action while messing with the quest).<br>
<br>
This has been posted before, but I'll run through it so no one has to dig:<br>
<br>
I open a trade window with the oil and have someone invis me...con Kandin, he's now indifferent. Click the give button and bam! get the note and staff.<br>
<br>
Head to Halas and con Dargon...she's indifferent. Hand her the note (not invised) and Arantir spawns. He's apprehensive. Open a trade window with the three staves and have someone invis me...con Arantir, he's now indifferent. Click the give button and bam! get the bag.<br>
<br>
Head to Temple of SolusekRo and con Solomen...he's apprehensive. Open a trade window with the bag and have someone invis me...con Solomen, he's now indiffent. Click the give button and bam! get the Staff of the Four.<br>
<br>
I also took the precaution of linking my items in chat and reporting myself before doing this (this is definitely not proof I have these items, but may speed things up if something got ate). Then I petitioned. The guide who showed up said they were aware of the problem, but there was nothing he could do. He then &quot;suggested&quot; I talk to other wizards and perhaps find a workaround for this problem. My impression is that he couldn't point blank tell me to invis up and do the quest, but they are aware of the invis trick working and, if not blatantly support, at least not penalize you for using this.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps people out,<br>
<br>
Shakarr Shockweaver<br>
60 Sorceror<br>
